# Electron Upgrade Rule

When upgrading Electron in the Cypress monorepo, follow this systematic approach to ensure all dependencies and configurations are properly updated.

## Prerequisites

Before starting, gather the following information:
- Current Electron version (from `/package.json`)
- Target Electron version (must be specified in chat prompt)
- New Node.js version bundled with target Electron
- New Chromium version bundled with target Electron

### Finding Version Information

**IMPORTANT**: The target Electron version, Chromium version, and Node.js verions must be specified in the chat prompt.

## Step 1: Update Core Electron Version

### Update Main Package.json
```bash
# Update the electron version in the root package.json
# File: /package.json
# Line: "electron": "36.8.1" -> "electron": "NEW_VERSION"
```

### Update Electron Package Dependencies
```bash
# Check if @electron/packager needs updating
# File: /packages/electron/package.json
# Update @electron/packager version if needed for compatibility
```

## Step 2: Update Node.js Version Synchronization

When Electron is upgraded, the bundled Node.js version often changes. Sync this across the monorepo:

### Node Version Files
```bash
# Update these files with the new Node.js version:
# File: /.node-version
# File: /.nvmrc
# Both should match the Node.js version bundled with the new Electron
```

### Package.json Engines
```bash
# File: /package.json
# Update engines.node to match the new Node.js version
# Example: "node": ">=22.18.0" -> "node": ">=NEW_NODE_VERSION"
```

### TypeScript Node Types
```bash
# Update @types/node throughout the monorepo
# The major version must match the Node.js version in .node-version
# Search for: "@types/node": "CURRENT_VERSION"
# Replace with: "@types/node": "NEW_VERSION"
```

## Step 3: Update Docker Configuration

### Docker Compose
```bash
# File: /docker-compose.yml
# Update the base-internal image reference:
# "cypress/base-internal:22.18.0-trixie" -> "cypress/base-internal:NEW_NODE_VERSION-trixie"
```

### CircleCI Workflows
```bash
# File: /.circleci/src/@workflows.yml
# Update base-internal image references:
# "base-internal-trixie: &base-internal-trixie cypress/base-internal:22.18.0-trixie" -> "base-internal-trixie: &base-internal-trixie cypress/base-internal:NEW_NODE_VERSION-trixie"
# "base-internal-yarn-berry: &base-internal-yarn-berry cypress/base-internal:22.18.0-yarn-berry" -> "base-internal-yarn-berry: &base-internal-yarn-berry cypress/base-internal:NEW_NODE_VERSION-yarn-berry"
# "base-internal-minimum-node: &base-internal-minimum-node cypress/base-internal:22.18.0" -> "base-internal-minimum-node: &base-internal-minimum-node cypress/base-internal:NEW_NODE_VERSION"
```

## Step 4: Update Dependencies

### Better SQLite3

```bash
# Check if better-sqlite3 needs updating for new Electron prebuilds looking through https://github.com/WiseLibs/better-sqlite3/commits/master/ to find the version number released after 'Prebuild for Election NEW_VERSION'.
# Files to update:
# /packages/server/package.json
# /packages/types/package.json
# Look for versions that support the new Electron version
```

### Node ABI Resolution
```bash
# File: /package.json
# Update node-abi resolution if needed:
# "node-abi": "4.9.0" -> "node-abi": "NEW_VERSION"
# Check https://github.com/electron/node-abi/releases for latest version
```

